sts/src/org.apache.camel/camel-kafka/4.20.0/src/test/java/org_apache_camel/camel_kafka/KafkaFetchRecordsTest.java`\n- Added `camel-core-engine` test dependency so the test can create a Camel context and Kafka endpoint.\n- Made the existing placeholder test class public to satisfy top-level test class convention.\n\nThe new test starts a Camel Kafka consumer with a real Kafka client through the public `KafkaClientFactory` API, then repeatedly calls `KafkaConsumer.healthStates()` to exercise `KafkaFetchRecords.healthState()`, reaching the dynamic-access paths in:\n- `KafkaFetchRecords.createConsumer(...)`\n- `KafkaFetchRecords.isReady(...)`\n\nI did not run or compile tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08622516edf788ea0169fd296bfd6081a0b3b6abc6f5f6ec8a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 552, "output": 750, "cacheRead": 45056, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46358, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778198877004, "responseId": "resp_08622516edf788ea0169fd295e80b881a08ed7adb13b354d13"}}
