flection fails.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added a focused test path for the remaining `KafkaFetchRecords.createConsumer(...)` dynamic-access call site.\n\nUpdated:\n\n- `tests/src/org.apache.camel/camel-kafka/4.20.0/src/test/java/org_apache_camel/camel_kafka/KafkaFetchRecordsTest.java`\n\nWhat changed:\n- Added `createConsumerReadsClientIdFromKafkaConsumerFieldWhenPropertyIsAbsent()`.\n- The test starts a Camel Kafka consumer through the public `KafkaClientFactory` API.\n- The factory returns a `MockConsumer` subclass with a `clientId` field and removes `client.id` from the Kafka properties.\n- This forces `KafkaFetchRecords.createConsumer(...)` through:\n\n```java\nconsumer.getClass().getDeclaredField(\"clientId\")\n```\n\n- The test asserts that `TaskHealthState#getClientId()` equals the reflected field value, proving that the dynamic-access path was reached.\n\nI did not run or compile tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08622516edf788ea0169fd2afc9a5481a0877404b6115a3752\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 541, "output": 713, "cacheRead": 53760, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 55014, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778199277000, "responseId": "resp_08622516edf788ea0169fd2aef76f481a0bce6f5df54904a3c"}, "toolResults": []}
